The paper discusses the design of a natural language interface for querying tables, which involves both data management and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which are both related to natural language processing. The paper also addresses the problem of users struggling to understand whether their query has been mapped correctly, which suggests a potential focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HCI). Finally, the paper proposes methods for explaining queries, which involves the use of machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI).
